      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RAKERO WARRIOR NZ (11) is in fine form having come from this row to win his last two outings. Returns to a circuit where he has yet to miss a place in five appearances, winning twice. Big chance to land the hat trick. AT THE DISTANCE (2) came from wider than this two back when he worked to the front for a win by 8m at Cranbourne. Solid when fourth since. This is the lowest draw he has had for some time. He can take advantage of that. KENNYWOULD (8) did a good job to finish runner-up after working last start at Maryborough, beaten 2 metres. Came from this barrier to score at Kilmore prior. Go well again. THE CHOOK (1) has come from wider to place in the last two outings. Can be competitive again from the ace draw. CENTURION DREAM (10) may need some luck from this barrier but strikes at 50 per cent here.",
